Here's How Your Investment Will Help Us
We're Focusing on Bringing New Products to Market & Going Global



More Products to Market

Our objective for the next three years is to introduce at least two new products per year to expand our product line. Our next product launch is scheduled for early 2017.            



International Expansion

The next phase of our growth includes expanding first into Canada, and then into Europe. Kickstarting our move into the international cycling market requires an injection of capital.

            



Customer Acquisition

A typical customer's acquisition cost is about ~9% of our revenue. The goal is to increase volume with our suppliers and thereby lower production costs to help reduce this percentage.

            



Recurring Revenue

We want to explore a bike-as-a-service, subscription-based model, where customers can pay a monthly fee for access to an EVELO bike, repairs, and theft protection.
            




Let's Change How We Move Around!


Dear Reader,
EVELO is growing fast! With over $3M in projected revenue this year and thousands of satisfied customers all over the United States, we've grown more than 60% this year alone. We have a strong, dedicated team in place and an amazing community of customers and Ambassadors all around the country.
      
We're proud that we reached this point on a fairly bootstrapped budget. My brother (and co-founder) and I started EVELO 4 years ago with just our personal savings. It's grown into a multi-million dollar, profitable company by focusing on the customer, developing beautiful, comfortable electric bikes, and creating an innovative distribution model. Our customers can customize their perfect bike in minutes and have it delivered 95% assembled directly to their door.
      
However, this is only the beginning. 
      

Our goal for EVELO has always been to make biking more accessible to everyone, by removing the common barriers that keep people from cycling. Whether those barriers are hills, fitness levels, age or even the simple inconvenience of arriving to a destination sweaty, EVELO bikes makes anything possible.
      
Moreover, we want to change the way that the traditional bicycle industry does business. By removing layers of distributors, sales reps, and brick-and-mortar dealers, our idea has always been to provide our customers with more value for every dollar they spend on the bike.
      
There is even more work to be done. We truly believe that electric bikes are the future of personal transportation and want to make them mainstream in North America. We are looking to release several new models next year, begin international expansion (starting with Canada), and introduce new ways to make owning an e-bike even more affordable.
      
To accomplish these goals faster and make EVELO a household brand, we are collaborating with a small group of investors that believe in the potential of electric bikes and want to be a part of this growing movement.
      
Now we're opening up investment in EVELO to all of those who share these goals. In the past, only wealthy investors and venture capitalists had the opportunity to buy stock in private companies like Google and Facebook before they went public. That just changed. The recent passage of the JOBS Act allows anyone to invest in private companies. 
      
As such, we invite you to take a look at our fundraising campaign.
      

           Sincerely,
        


            Boris Mordkovich, CEO
        


 
